FBIS3-42239 "jptot006__l94051" JPRS-TOT-94-006-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 9 February 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA `Retribution' Group Threatens To Blow Up Yakutsk Vital Facilities Ransom Demanded LD0202134494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1200 GMT 2 Feb 94 LD0202134494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Retribution [Vozmezdiye] terrorist group has demanded that the Yakutsk authorities hand over $500,000 and 500 million rubles at the city's airport on 4 February. Otherwise they are threatening to blow up facilities providing vital services to the capital of Yakutia. According to INTERFAX, a cassette recording with these demands was handed in to the mayor's office by an unidentified person. Employees of the Ministries of Security and Internal Affairs are searching for the criminals.
